This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with evaluating automatic speech recognition systems for dialectal speech input. It also involves the use of unsupervised mining of spelling variants from social media, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Retrieval (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper involves manual analysis, which could fall under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of spelling variants also involves Information Retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the paper deals with evaluating ASR systems, which could fall under the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY).
